cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with detecting homoglyph attacks, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses a Siamese convolutional neural network (CNN) to detect visual similarity, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a neural network also suggests that the paper may fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses KD-Trees for similarity searches, which is a data structure commonly used in computational geometry and nearest neighbor search, suggesting a possible fit under neural networks (cs.NE).
